==English==

===Noun===
'''pimp''' (''plural:'' '''[[pimps]]''')
# A person who [[solicit]]s customers for [[prostitution]] and acts as manager for [[prostitute]]s; a [[panderer]].
#:''The '''pimp''' beat one of his girls up for not making enough money in one night.''
# (''slang, [[w:AAVE|AAVE]]'') Man who can easily attract women; a [[player]]/[[playa]].

====Translations====
'''prostitution solicitor'''
*[[w:Spanish language|Spanish]]: [[chulo]] {{m}}
*[[w:Portuguese language|Portuguese]] [[safado]] {{m}}
*Romanian: proxenet {{m}}, peşte {{m}}
*Swahili: [[buzi]]
*Swedish: [[hallick]]
*Finnish: [[sutenööri]] (1)

===Verb (intransitive)===
'''pimp''' ([[pimps]], [[pimping]], [[pimped]])
# To act as a procurer of [[prostitute]]s; to [[pander]].
# (''Medical profession slang'') When the attending physician asks an impossible to answer question of a resident or medical student.
# (''US, [[w:AAVE|AAVE]]'') To excessively [[customise]] something, especially a vehicle, according to [[ghetto]] [[standard|standards]].
#:''You '''pimped''' out that [[Ac]] [[f'real]], [[dawg]].''

====Translations====

*Finnish: [[toimia sutenöörinä]] (1)

===Verb (transitive)===
'''pimp'''
#To [[prostitute]] someone.
#:''The smooth-talking, tall man with heavy gold bracelets claimed he could '''pimp''' anyone.''

